<span id="freeTextContainer17547875348381363184">This is a thought provoking book that actually manages to explain a lot about morality from the scientific view point. However there are some views that I completely disagree with (e.g. the author argues that free trade is good; in some cases it is, but there are many scenarios where it actually does more harm than good) and some facts are either wrong or outdated (e.g. the author states that second hand smoking doesn&apos;t cause cancer; it does).</span>
  <span id="freeText17547875348381363184" style="display:none">This is a thought provoking book that actually manages to explain a lot about morality from the scientific view point. However there are some views that I completely disagree with (e.g. the author argues that free trade is good; in some cases it is, but there are many scenarios where it actually does more harm than good) and some facts are either wrong or outdated (e.g. the author states that second hand smoking doesn't cause cancer; it does).</span>
